The Chronicle Nqobile Tshili, Chronicle Reporter THE public has ignored calls to illegally shutdown the country with peace prevailing countrywide as members of the public go about their business. Anti-riot police among other security players have been deployed in strategic areas to thwart any illegal protests. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-607272" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/no-shutdown-2.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/no-shutdown-2.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/no-shutdown-2-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> Regime change proponents under the banner Pachedu called for a national shutdown but it is business as usual as shops and other businesses go about their operations as usual in Bulawayo and other places. In a statement posted on social media platform Twitter, Zimbabwe Republic Police said peace is prevailing across the country. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-607270" src="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/No-shutdown.jpg" alt="" width="680" height="380" srcset="https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/No-shutdown.jpg 680w, https://www.chronicle.co.zw/wp-content/uploads/sites/3/2022/05/No-shutdown-360x200.jpg 360w" sizes="(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px" /> “The ZRP reports that the situation in the country is normal. The public is urged to report anyone trying to intimidate, harass or threaten members of the public who are peacefully conducting their normal day-to-day activities. Police are ready to ensure that peace continues to prevail throughout the country,” read the statement. @nqotshili